AKURE – A senior lecturer at the Obafemi Awolowo University (OAU) Ile Ife, Prof. Jerome Elutayo Elusiyan, has been shot dead by suspected gunmen at Iruekpen, along Benin-Ekpoma Expressway in Esan West Local Government Area of Edo State. He was the Chairman, Medical Advisory Committee, ObafemiAwolowo University Teaching Hospital Complex, (OAUTH), Ile-Ife. The gunmen on Friday shot the professor of Paediatric and Child Health with his driver, who sustained serious gunshot injuries. Confirming the incident, one the professor’s cousins, Mr. Tayo Ayoshile disclosed that he, (Prof.Elusiyan) was killed while on his way from Benin. He said the late professor was an external examiner at Iruua Specialist Hospital (ISTH) where he went to supervise medical students writing professional examinations. According to him, “He was returning home when he was shot dead during the attack while his driver sustained gunshot injuries. “Uncle Jerome was a rare gem and an erudite that for over 30 years has also been a freedom fighter. “We are very sad by his gruesome death. Love and soul are immortal, while death is the only horizon and the horizon is nothing to save the limit of our sight. “His death is a shock to every sons and daughters of Oke Igbo here in Ondo State and we can only join to sympathize with all the OAU members if staff, friends and entire family.” Spokesperson of OAUTHC, Kemi Fasoto, also confirmed the incident.